Authors analysed 359 cases with Down's syndrome and congenital heart defects 
registered between 1974-1997 in Hungary. The total death rate was 19.9% (70 
cases). Mortality in the operated group (85 cases) was 10.5% (9 patients), in 
the non-operated group (274 cases) 22.2% (61 patients). The death rate was lower 
