palliation + reconstruction (15.3%), or in the group with only palliative 
procedure (20%). These results indicate that the life expectancy of infants and 
children with Down's syndrome and congenital heart disease after early primary 
reconstructive procedure is the same as in Down syndrome patients without 
cardiac defects. The prognosis depends on the patient's social circumstances. 
The results after correct surgical procedure in patients with the same cardiac 
defect are similar to that of the patients with or without Down's syndrome.

